TY  - JOUR
T1  - Blau's Theory of Structural Differentiation Revisited: A Theory of Structural Change or Scale?
AU  - Cullen, John B.
AU  - Anderson, Kenneth S.
AU  - Baker, Douglas D.
Y1  - 1986/06/01
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256186
DO  - 10.5465/256186
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 203
EP  - 229
VL  - 29
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The major objective of this study was to determine if Blau's (1970) theory of structural differentiation better captures differences in scale between organizations or structural changes within organizations. Data gathered on 134 Ph.D.-granting universities over nine years permitted us to compare results of within-organizations tests of Blau's theory with those from both cross-sectional and longitudinal between-organization tests. The findings suggest that the theory's power lies in explaining structural differences between organizations rather than in explaining structural change.
AB  - The major objective of this study was to determine if Blau's (1970) theory of structural differentiation better captures differences in scale between organizations or structural changes within organizations. Data gathered on 134 Ph.D.-granting universities over nine years permitted us to compare results of within-organizations tests of Blau's theory with those from both cross-sectional and longitudinal between-organization tests. The findings suggest that the theory's power lies in explaining structural differences between organizations rather than in explaining structural change.
